hom Raymond Massey called "the greatest exterior camera artist in the world," enhanced the work of such major filmmakers as Cecil B. De Mille, Alexander Korda, Robert Flaherty, Alfred Hitchcock, Michael Powell, and Otto Preminger. Life through a Lens, the personal journey of a great adventurer and artist, will be of interest not only to film historians but to anyone captivated by the cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aHadley, Anita B., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356982940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773569829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773569829/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles